This program initializes `x` to `0` and then reads from `std::cin`. What does it print if the user enters `42`?

```cpp
#include <iostream>

int main()
{
    int x = 0;
    std::cin >> x;
    std::cout << x << '\n';
    return 0;
}
```

What does this well-formed program print?

```cpp
